Package net.automatalib.serialization

Interface ModelDeserializer<M>

  • Type Parameters:
    M - the type of objects implementing classes can deserialize
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    DOTInputModelDeserializer<S,​I,​M>, InputModelDeserializer<I,​M>, InputModelSerializationProvider<I,​OUT,​IN>, SerializationProvider<OUT,​IN>, SimpleAutomatonDeserializer<S,​I>, SimpleAutomatonSerializationProvider<S,​I>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractFSM2MealyParser, AUTSerializationProvider, DOTGraphParser, DOTMutableAutomatonParser, FSM2DFAParser, FSM2MealyParserAlternating, FSM2MealyParserIO, LearnLibV2Serialization, SAFSerializationDFA, SAFSerializationNFA, TAFSerializationDFA, TAFSerializationMealy
    public interface ModelDeserializer<M>
    A generic interface for formalizing an arbitrary deserializer for a given model type.

      • readModel

        M readModel​(InputStream is)
     throws IOException
        Reads the contents from the given input stream and de-serializes it into a model instance.

        Note: the input stream will not be closed.

        Parameters:
        is - the input stream to read data from
        Returns:
        the de-serialized model
        Throws:
        IOException - if an error occurred while reading from the stream
        FormatException - if the content of the stream was not in the expected format
